Day 3 of my Java learning journey.

Today I focused on the core building blocks of programming.

I learned about variables, identifiers, and data types.

Understanding variables helped me see how data is stored in memory.
Identifiers made it clear how we name variables and follow proper rules.
Data types showed how different kinds of data (int, float, char, etc.) are handled in a program.

These concepts may look basic, but they are the foundation of everything in programming.

The more I learn, the more I realize how important strong basics are.

